article_teaser_type.description: Fires in conjunction with magazine_feed. This is used for paywall to see if users will authenticate to continue reading the article teaser. (prop27)

author_name.description: Name of the author who wrote the article

author_type.description: The contributor network of the author eg. 'time staff', 'contributor', etc.

available_app_ids.description: List of available app ids subscriber has access to, Text (comma-separated list of app names)

browse_refine_type.description: Array of browse/search refine types eg. ['Content Type', 'Rooms and Areas']

browse_refine_value.description: Array of browse/search refine values eg. ['Gallery', 'Dining Areas']

bundle_id.description: Bundle id, 3 digit numeric (specific subscriber bundle within a tier)

channel.description: Brand name of the web property (channel) eg. sunset, fortune, etc.

click_id.description: Event variable: Identifier for the user action click eg. pin-it-ctr (prop35, evar43)

content_id.description: Unique identifier of the page content

content_package.description: Name of the package containing the content

content_package_id.description: Unique ID of the package containing the content

content_package_section.description: Name of the section within a package (used in s.pageName) eg. best trips, by destination

country_code.description: Country Code eg. us, uk, mx, ca, jp, etc.

currency_code.description: Currency code associated with the page eg. USD, EUR, etc.

customer_country.description: The country code of the address in the order eg. US, CA, UK

customer_state.description: The State of the address in the order eg. CA

customer_zip.description: The postal code of the address in the order eg. 92101

event_name.description: Tealium variable to identify unique events eg. click_action, search_submit, click_tout, etc.

franchise_name.description: Name of the franchise, on franchise pages

friendly_url.description: The actual URL of the page, might be different than the URL in the browser location bar

has_continuous_service.description: Customer is enrolled in continuous service, True or False

has_donor.description: Customer has any donor contracts, True or False

is_agent_subscription.description: Indicates if the top (most recent) active contract is an agency contract.

is_bill_me.description: Customer opted to be billed separately at order time, True or False

is_giftee.description: Customer has a giftee (recipient) contract, True or False

is_logged_in.description: Whether logged-in or out to site (paid or gated content), eg. Yes or No

is_renewable.description: Indicates if the customer's account is eligible for renewal, True or False

language_code.description: Language Code eg.  us, es, fr, etc.

login_status.description: Determines if the visitor has an account with the site

magazine_cover_title.description: Main cover story on the hardcopy of the magazine

magazine_feed.description: Categorizes if the article is published in the print magazine or not.

magazine_issue_date.description: Date of when the hardcopy of the magazine is published

markets.description: Used to differentiate the markets page from the other templates.

page_name.description: The friendly name of the page displayed

page_number.description: Page number for multi-page galleries eg. 2

primary_tag.description: Keyword used on the pages to increase ranking for SEO

publish_date.description: Date of when the article was published.

rr_modules.description: RR and Article Divider Modules eg. 'rr-related|rr-ad'

search_keyword.description: The term entered into the site search tool

search_results.description: The number of results returned on the search page

secondary_renewal_offer.description: Alternate renewal effort key, Effort key or 'blank'

site_display_format.description: Which format of the site has been viewed: desktop, tablet, or mobile .

site_section1.description: The first hierarchy level of the page within the site's ecosystem.

site_section2.description: The second hierarchy level of the page within the site's ecosystem.

site_section3.description: The third hierarchy level of the page within the site's ecosystem.

site_section4.description: The fourth hierarchy level of the page within the site's ecosystem.

site_theme.description: Distinguishes whether the page is using the new CMS or old CMS

slide_title.description: On gallery slide shows, the title of the gallery slide displayed

subscriber_id.description: Subscriber's ID, numeric id (not needed for targeting)

subscriber_type.description: Type of subscriber (ie. Apple, B & N, employee) eg dau-btf, dos-apple, trial-active, etc.

subscription_status.description: Current status of account eg. Active, Expired, Cancelled, KU

tag_keywords.description: Keyword terms associated with the page content, pipe delimited eg. 'careers|taskers|chores' etc.

tcm_effort_key.description: Subscription attributes combined into one string (evar25)

tcm_keycode.description: Used to capture keycode for TIHE and Oxmoor orders

tcm_newsletter_optin.description: Used to capture newsletter optin sku on Subs3 forms

tcm_mag_code.description: A 2-letter magazine brand descriptor used by the Subs3 system

tcm_order_id.description: The unique identifier for the finalized purchase

tcm_order_shipping_amount.description: The shipping amount charged in the order eg. '4.00'

tcm_order_subtotal.description: The subtotal of the products in the order, excludes shipping, tax, and discounts eg. '42.92'

tcm_order_tax_amount.description: The tax amount charged in the order

tcm_order_total.description: The grand total of the order, including shipping, tax, and discounts eg. '46.92'

tcm_order_type.description: The type of order, either 'gift' or 'self'

tcm_page_flow.description: The type of page within the subs3 checkout cross sell flow eg. offer, continue, thankyou

tcm_payment_method.description: The method of payment eg. paypal, amex, visa, etc.

tcm_prefix.description: TCM Prefix identifying the site/microsite eg. TCM_SU, TCM_BACKISSUES_SI

tcm_product_name.description: Array of product names in the page, cart or order eg. ['SI PRESENTS: SEATTLE SEAHAWKS 2014 CHAMPIONS', '2015 SWIMSUIT ISSUE - AMERICA THE BEAUTIFUL']

tcm_product_price.description: Array of product prices on the product, cart and order eg. ['19.95', '7.99']

tcm_product_quantity.description: Array of product quantities on the cart and order eg. ['1', '2']

tcm_product_sku.description: Array of product skus in the product page (single sku), cart or order eg. ['su-12for16cc0115'] or ['SIHB14NFLSB', 'SI20150220SPEC']

tcm_product_sku_options.description: Array of all product skus available on the product detail page eg. ['SISWIM15VNECKL', 'SISWIM15VNECKM', 'SISWIM15VNECKS', 'SISWIM15VNECKXS'

tcm_shipping_method.description: The method of shipment eg. standard, express, priority, etc.

tcm_variation_id.description: The variation of the microsite (evar75) eg. 'version A'

tcm_xsell_microsite.description: The microsite value related to the confirmed upsell product when the tcm_microsite has a different value (usually when tcm_page_type=upsell_order) eg. gf-cfxsell1214

tcm_xsell_page_flow.description: The page flow related to the confirmed upsell product when the tcm_upsell_microsite is populated eg. nextoffer

template_type.description: Template type (aka content type) for the current page  eg. index page, subchannel, gallery, franchise, etc.

ticker_symbol.description: Used to differentiate the markets' company page from the other templates.

tier_level.description: Tier level, 2 digit numeric (subscriber tier e.g. print=20, digital=20, all access=50, VIP=80)

total_amount_due.description: Total outstanding balance on customer's account, Number ('$XXX.XX') or 'blank'

video_asset_id.description: The name of the video played (evar53)

video_franchise.description: The name of the video played (evar57)

video_name.description: The name of the video played (evar6,prop48)

video_player.description: The name of the video player used eg. Brightcove (evar58)

video_player_type.description: The type of the video played (evar59)

video_segment.description: The name of the video played (evar56)
